---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
    <section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-6 bg-white min-h-screen">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-[#423c3b] mb-6 leading-tight">
                Tour to the Ceremonial Center of Cahuachi
            </h1>

            <img src="/cahuachi.jpg" alt="Cahuachi Ceremonial Center" class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg mb-8" />

            <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-lg">
                <p>
                    The tour to the <strong>Cahuachi Ceremonial Center</strong> offers a fascinating journey through one of the most important archaeological sites of the Nasca culture.
                    Located about 28 kilometers from the city of Nasca, this complex served as a religious and ceremonial hub between the 1st and 5th centuries A.D.
                    It is recognized as the worldâ€™s largest mud-brick ceremonial center.
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-bus text-[#a59f89] mr-2"></i>
                            Departure from Nasca:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            The tour begins with a vehicle transfer from the city of Nazca to Cahuachi, crossing desert landscapes and fertile valleys. The journey takes approximately 45 minutes.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-landmark text-[#a59f89] mr-2"></i>
                            Guided tour of the archaeological site:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Upon arrival, a specialized guide leads visitors through the complex's main structures, including the Great Pyramid, ceremonial plazas, religious precincts, and residential areas. Details are provided about the rituals performed there, the adobe ceremonial architecture, and the most significant archaeological discoveries.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-mountain text-[#a59f89] mr-2"></i>
                            Observation of the environment:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            The connection between the site and its natural surroundings is highlighted, including its proximity to the Nazca lines and its symbolic relationship with the Nazca River.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-university text-[#a59f89] mr-2"></i>
                            Optional visit to the Antonini Museum:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Some tours include a complementary visit to the Antonini Museum, where archaeological artifacts recovered from Cahuachi are on display, including ceramics, textiles, and mummified human remains.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base pt-4">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Approximate duration:</strong> 3 to 4 hours
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="pt-4">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">
                        <i class="fas fa-sun mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i> 
                        Recommendations:
                    </h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base">
                        <li>
                            Bring sunscreen, a hat, and water.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Wear light clothing and comfortable shoes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Camera to capture the impressive landscape and architecture.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mt-10">
                    <a href="/#tours" class="text-[#423c3b] px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border border-[#423c3b] text-base font-medium hover:bg-[#423c3b] hover:text-[#cbc4ae] transition">
                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left mr-2"></i> Back to Itineraries
                    </a>
                    <a href="https://wa.link/0voy2n" class="bg-[#423c3b] text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg text-base font-medium hover:bg-[#3d3433] transition" target="_blank">
                        <i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i>
                        Request Reservation
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
